Dear Doc Del:<br><br>
Your perspectives are a welcome form of feedback..and I have listened.  It is interesting to see my actions through the eyes of others.  It does not mean that I have to agree or disagree with you or others, however the tact with which you present an argument is always a plus.<br>
The intended meanings embodied in our transmissions are not always the same meanings received by those we address.<br>
I find the first four paragraphs of your post above to be constructive and positive.<br>
It is your last paragraph, that suggests that anyone has been excluded by &quot;the handful of vets who have dominated these pages these last few months,&quot; that troubles me.  Who has been excluded?  The vile exchanges between Spatz and everyone else has created an environment that many would want to avoid.  The evident bonding that has occured between the &quot;handful of vets&quot; has not discouraged but has encouraged the participation of others..including non-vets, ladies, anti-war protestors etc.<br>
In posting here or on any public forum one is at risk of being criticized or confirmed.  The decision to post or not post is a personal choice.  The manner in which one posts may be deemed acceptable or unacceptable, but no one needs permission or invitation to interact here.<br>
Often, one can see the mercurial rise and fall of emotions that seem to generate from a diversity of topics.  Always there appears to be tangents and surprises.<br>
The Meir principle, the sharing of common values, is the impetus here for brotherly bonding and tolerance.  Where opposing values collide there is the opposite result, often resulting in a decay of communication.<br>
I would not censure or control anyone's thoughts or values here to accomodate someone else who is too insecure, uncertain or angry to postulate their own feelings.  <br>
If you or anyone has been reluctant to post here because of what I have had to say.. then that is a terrible shame.  I would like to help them out, but I didn't see which way they came in!<br><br>
I say what I mean and I mean what I say..in a serious mode. What I say in jest is usually communicated in a fashion that leaves no doubt in anyone's mind that it is indeed humor.. and not serious ridicule!<br><br>
I personally hope you join us, as well as others choosing to join us, but if you don't or I don't, someone else will come along and the site will continue.<br><br>
Futhermore, I don't share your proclaimation that &quot;the handful of vets&quot; has fostered or perpetuated the problems that have occured here recently nor should they modify their indignance to the personal assaults from the likes of Spatz.<br><br>
Again, I pray that your health and strength are improving.  You remain special to me because of you personal sacrifices in Vietnam and I wish you the very best in this holiday season and the coming year.<br><br>
Welcome Home, Doc Del<br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>

